<div class="elementor-widget-container">
<h2 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">What is kAIron?</h2> </div>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-40305f9 elementor-invisible elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="40305f9" data-element_type="widget" data-settings="{&quot;_animation&quot;:&quot;fadeInLeft&quot;}" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
<div class="elementor-widget-container">
<div class="elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix">
<p style="text-align: justify;">kAIron is a web based microservices driven suite that helps you create &amp; train contextual AI assistants at scale. It is designed to make the lives of those who work with AI-assistants easy by giving them a no-coding web interface to adapt, train, test and maintain such assistants.</p><p style="text-align: justify;">kAIron is currently built on the RASA framework. While RASA focuses on the technology of chatbots itself, kAIron, on the other hand, focuses on technology that deals with the pre-processing of data that are needed by this framework. These include question augmentation and generation of knowledge graphs that can be used to automatically generate intents, questions and responses.</p> </div>
</div>

<div class="elementor-widget-container">
<h2 class="elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">What can it do?</h2> </div>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-bcda04a elementor-invisible elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="bcda04a" data-element_type="widget" data-settings="{&quot;_animation&quot;:&quot;fadeInRight&quot;}" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
<div class="elementor-widget-container">
<div class="elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix">
<p style="text-align: justify;">One of the biggest barriers to the adoption of chatbots within organizations is adapting contextual AI assistants to specific domains. This means extensive work creating intents by going through documentation, testing accuracy of responses, etc. kAIron’s aim is to provide a no-coding self-service framework that helps users achieve this. These are the features in the 0.1 version –</p><ul><li style="text-align: justify;">Easy to use UI for adding and editing Intents, Questions and Responses</li><li style="text-align: justify;">Question augmentation to auto-generate questions and enrich training data</li><li style="text-align: justify;">Model Training and Deployment from Interface</li><li style="text-align: justify;">Metrics for model performance</li></ul> </div>
</div>
</div>

<p><strong>kAIron is built for two personas:</strong></p><ul><li>Teams and Individuals who want an easy no-code interface to create, train, test and deploy chatbots.</li><li>Teams who want to host the chatbot trainer in-house. They can build it using docker-compose.</li></ul><p>kAIron’s released under the Apache 2.0 license. You can find the source here – <a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/digiteinfotech/kairon" rel="noopener">https://github.com/digiteinfotech/kairon</a>. Our team’s current focus within NLP is Knowledge Graphs – Do let us know if you are interested.</p> </div>
